## History / Discovered In

This rule was originally extracted from production findings in the LeadScraper project, where each of the three prohibition classes was documented with specific source-file locations and corrective patches. The detailed historical catalogue — sprint references, file paths, and root-cause analysis per finding — is preserved in **ADR-004** in this repository.

For consumer projects, the relevant signal is the **classification** above: every IO-touching pull request should be reviewed against the three prohibitions, with zero new instances expected on protected branches.
